<title>USA: Shiloh, MTD say propose $19 shr deal.</title>
<headline>Shiloh, MTD say propose $19 shr deal.</headline>
<dateline>MANSFIELD, Ohio 1997-06-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shiloh Industries Inc and MTD Products Inc said Thursday certain Shiloh stockholders are in favor of a $19-per-share acquisition by MTD of the shares of Shiloh that MTD does not already own.</p>
<p>MTD owns approximately 36 percent of Shiloh's outstanding common stock, the company said.</p>
<p>Shiloh said it intends to form a special board committee to consider and negotiate terms of the proposed transaction, but there can be no assurance that any transaction would be completed.</p>
<p>The company was not immediately available to comment.</p>
